    <section>

    

    <heading>The XML nodes below should be indented nicely and coloured blue</heading>

<para>If you want to select a set of nodes from an XML document

you should start with the top node and select on down.</para>





<para>ex: if you have this XML</para>



<node>&lt;root&gt;

  <node>&lt;sub1&gt;

    <node>&lt;sub2&gt;

      <node>&lt;target&gt;the answer&lt;/target&gt;</node>

    &lt;/sub2&gt;</node>

  &lt;/sub1&gt;</node>

&lt;/root&gt;</node>



<para>then this XPATH</para>



<pre>/root/sub1/sub2/target</pre>



<para>will return this text</para>



<pre>the answer</pre>



